<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9988> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9988" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Sicilia de Poeneis. MRR I.208, Itgenshorst no. 132, Rich no. 131." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8847> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8847" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 725" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1184> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1184" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire, but Manlius' cognomen is spelled ATEIC); cf. Liv. Per. 19. See Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1177> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1177" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (name entire); Degrassi 42f., 116, 436f. The first Dictator to lead an army outside of Italy (Liv. Per. 19; Zon. 8.15; cf. Dio 36.34.3; Flor. 1.18.12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1150> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1150" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Polyb. 1.38.7; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.14; see Degrassi, 42f., 116, 434f. The Consuls brought a new fleet to Sicily, and were repulsed at Drepanum, but captured Panormus and other towns (Polyb. 1.38.5-10; Diod. 23.18.3-5; Zon. 8.14; cf. Frontin. Str. 4.7.9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1149> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1149" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The cognomen Caiatinus appears as Caletino in Chr. 354, Catatione in Fast. Hyd., {Gr} in Chr. Pasc., and {Gr} in Zonaras." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1142> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1142" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Celebrated as Pr(aetor) a triumph ex Sicilia de Poenis (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 548; cf. Cic. Pis. 58; Auct. Vir. Ill. 39)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1141> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1141" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr., the text of Act. Tr., is supplemented as Pr(ocos.) in RE, having regard for the pattern of office revealed in the triumph of Aquillius Florus in 258, but Pro Cos. and Pro Pr. are regularly written in Act. Tr. in the case of promagistrates. Pr. in this sense would be unique in the preserved fragments of the stone. In official careers before the Second Punic war the praetorship often followed the consulship. See Degrassi 76f., 548, who reads Pr(aetor); Maxis 15; Stella Maranca 294." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1133> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1133" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Polyb. 1.24.9; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Zon. 8.12; Degrassi 42f., 115f., 434f. Atilius succeeded Florus, attacked Panormus, captured Mytistratus and other towns, but failed to win the Lipari islands (Polyb. 1.24.8-13; Zon. 8.12; cf. Cato, fr. 83 Peter; Diod. 23.3.9-10; Liv. Per. 17; Frontin. Str. 1.5.15-4.5.10; Flor. 1.18.12-14, who confuses Atilius' offices and the towns captured; Auct. Vir. Ill. 39; Oros. 4.8.1-5). Polybius places Sulpicius in Sicily (1.24.9), but he reduced Sardinia, defeated a Punic fleet, and celebrated a triumph over the Carthaginians and the Sardinians (Act. Tr., Degrassi 76f., 548; cf. Zon. 8.12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1132> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1132" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In the Fast. Cap. and Act. Tr. (for 257) Atilius' name appears as Caiatinus, but in the literary tradition almost invariably as Calatinus, cognomina drawn respectively from two neighboring towns in Campania. It is probable that literary tradition would tend to assimilate Caiatinus to Calatinus, the more important town. See Münzer, APF 57-61, who remains uncertain which is correct. Degrassi (115f.) favors Caiatinus." .
